<body>
  <h1>Crimson Petals — Chapter 2: "Ashes of Rebellion"</h1>

  <div class="chapter">
    <strong>Page 1:</strong><br>
    Aiko trains alone in a ruined hall, her hands bruised.<br>
    <em>"Har chot ek naya sawaal uthati thi… kya main roshni laa sakti hoon?"</em><br><br>

    <strong>Page 2:</strong><br>
    Takeshi watches her from shadows.<br>
    Rebel whispers: “Yeh ladki ziddi hai… par zaroori bhi.”<br>
    Takeshi: “Uske andar uski maa ka khoon hai.”<br><br>

    <strong>Page 3:</strong><br>
    Yuuto draws the sun with broken crayons in a dark room.<br>
    Yuuto: “Main dhoop bana sakta hoon… kaagaz par hi sahi.”<br><br>

    <strong>Page 4:</strong><br>
    A regime broadcast blares:<br>
    <em>“Surya Samarthakon ko chhupne ki jagah nahi milegi.”</em><br><br>

    <strong>Page 5:</strong><br>
    Rebel outpost is attacked by drones. Chaos, smoke, screams.<br>
    Takeshi shouts: “Aiko! Yeh tumhara mission nahi hai!”<br>
    Aiko runs into the fire.<br><br>

    <strong>Page 6:</strong><br>
    Aiko saves a child from debris. Her red scarf catches fire.<br>
    She removes it and wraps it around the child.<br>
    <em>“Roshni kapdon mein nahi… dil mein hoti hai.”</em><br><br>

    <strong>Page 7:</strong><br>
    Back at the base, rebels look at her with respect.<br>
    Takeshi gives her a communicator.<br>
    “Agla mission: Tower ke neeche ke logon tak pahuchna.”<br><br>

    <strong>Page 8:</strong><br>
    Aiko stares at the dark tower from a ruined wall.<br>
    <em>“Andhera kab tak jeetega?”</em><br>
    <strong>To Be Continued...</strong>
  </div>
